'''Mimatsuhiko Shrine''' (みまつひこじんじゃ) is a {{ill|lt=shrine|Q845945|qid=Q845945|1=Shinto shrine}} enshrined in {{ill|lt=Sanagōchi|Q1206355|qid=Q1206355|1=Sanagōchi, Tokushima}}, {{ill|lt=Tokushima Prefecture|Q160734|qid=Q160734|1=Tokushima Prefecture}}.

=== History ===
The founding year is unknown. The enshrined Mimatsuhiko Iroto no Mikoto is a pioneering deity of Sanagōchi. It is said that in the era of {{ill|lt=Emperor Seimu|Q316672|qid=Q316672|1=Emperor Seimu}}, the ninth-generation descendant {{ill|UNKNOWN|lt=Karasokeni|1=UNKNOWN}} became {{ill|lt=Naga no Kuni no Miyatsuko|Q21653903|qid=Q21653903|1=Naga no Kuni no Miyatsuko}} and originally enshrined this deity at the middle slope of Nagamine (present-day Shimo-Nakamine). In the era of {{ill|lt=Emperor Daigo|Q329753|qid=Q329753|1=Emperor Daigo}}, it was listed as a {{ill|lt=small state-offered shrine|Q11064932|qid=Q11064932|lt=kokuhei shōsha|1=Engishiki Jinmyōchō}}.

=== Enshrined deity ===
* {{ill|lt=Ama-no-Yatsuhatsu-tsuhiko no Mikoto|Q86728909|qid=Q86728909|lt=Mimatsuhiko Iroto no Mikoto|1=Mimatsuhiko-Irodo-no-Mikoto}}（みまつひこいろとのみこと）

=== Access ===
* About 40 minutes by car from {{ill|lt=Tokushima Station|Q860775|qid=Q860775|1=Tokushima Station}} on {{ill|lt=JR Shikoku|Q496531|qid=Q496531|lt=JR|1=Shikoku Railway Company}}.

